The paper deals with algorithms for decremental single-source reachability and strongly connected components in directed planar graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the focus is on algorithmic solutions, we can eliminate cs.SI as a likely sub-category. Among the remaining four, cs.DS and cs.CG seem the most likely, as they deal with algorithmic solutions for graph-related problems. cs.DM and cs.GT are also possible, as they deal with theoretical aspects of graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS and cs.CG, followed by cs.DM and cs.GT.
